# ============================================================================
# Notes on Package Differences & Alternatives
# ============================================================================

# Packages with different names:
# - fd -> fd-find (command: fdfind)
# - bat -> bat (same name, different repo sometimes)
# - exa -> exa (may need snap or cargo)

# Packages requiring manual installation:
# - eza (replacement for exa)
# - starship (install via curl)
# - gh (GitHub CLI - via official repo)
# - docker (via official repo)
# - nodejs/npm (via NodeSource)
# - rustup/cargo (via rustup.rs)
# - nvm (for Node version management)

# macOS-specific packages (no Linux equivalent):
# - amethyst (use i3, sway, or similar window managers)
# - hammerspoon (use autokey or similar)
# - karabiner-elements (use xmodmap or setxkbmap)
# - sizeup (use window manager features)
# - macos-trash (use 'trash-cli' package)

# GUI applications requiring Flatpak/Snap:
# - Blender: snap install blender --classic
# - VS Code: snap install code --classic
# - Postman: snap install postman
# - Skype: snap install skype --classic